docs.lead_paragraph: Will big banks keep clocking big profits? JPMorgan, Citigroup and Wells Fargo kicked off earnings season for the largest United States banks on Friday, revealing another quarter of strong growth despite a relatively small increase in lending. Bank of America reports its second-quarter results on Monday morning, followed by Goldman Sachs on Tuesday and Morgan Stanley on Wednesday. Trading revenue won't be what it was during the busy beginning of 2018, but the banks are trying to make up for lackluster markets by cultivating other businesses like wealth management and consumer finance.

headline.main: Banks Report Earnings, and Google Faces Antitrust Fines
headline.print_headline: Banks Report Earnings, And Google Is Facing Antitrust Fines in Europe
